      "message": "1) ctx.Error accepts a format, while this is a string. It means that the error message happens to have %s, it will be rendered incorrectly. To prevent such mistakes, usually functions that accept a format end with \"f\", e.g. fmt.Errorf, logging.Infof, fmt.Printf, etc.\n2) here we have an error, generates a string out of it by calling .Error(), pass to ctx.Error which creates an error again (L111) but loosing all of its information (stack, etc).\n3) word error is repeated 3 times\n4) (not your CL) to prevent (1)\n\nplease\n\n1) rename existing ctx.Error to ctx.Errorf (in a separate CL)\n2) add ctx.Error that accepts an error. It will require refactoring of ctx.Errorf. It is currently prepends context (file, element info) to the error. This can be done using errors.Annotate(err, \"%s\", ctx) without loosing error info",
